  "text": ". The crux of the proof applies an inequality relating the trace norms of the first level (matrix) Fourier-coefficients of a matrix-valued function to its average trace norm (see Lemma 5.3). The crucial observation is that the norms of the first level Fourier coefficients of the above defined F can be lower bounded using the LDC property. The result then follows by combining this with the trivial upper bound on the average norm of F . This proof loosely follows an argument of [CITATION_1] used for binary (non linear) LDCs and is inspired by work of [CITATION_2] linking LDCs to geometry of Banach spaces.",
